Package: GbmExplainR
Type: Package
Title: Decompose gbm predictions into feature contributions + bias
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Richard Angell <richardangell37@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Richard Angell <richardangell37@gmail.com>
Description: Package to explain gbm predictions. Works with the gbm package. The main feature of this package is the ability to decompose gbm predictions into feature contributions + bias. There is also functionality to plot tree structures along with terminal node paths for specific observations.
Depends: gbm, igraph
License: GNU General Public License v3.0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
